column5: Anyone ever catch one of these before? I caught this one on Sunday.
My eyes tell me that ain't no buffalo. Wrong dorsal.
ok ok a smallmouth buffalo then.

Well I might as well call it a day then, not likely it'll happen twice in one day....LOL  I've hit a few of them as well as Buffalo in the Grand as incidental catches and usually (accidentally) foul hooked.
Quillback sucker. The long dorsal spine gives it away. They also have a very distinctive looking eye, with a vertical dark bar running through it.
All kinds of weird lookin critters in our lakes. Very cool looking catch
Billions of them come spring time in the south shore Erie trib's.
Funny you say that because this one was foul hooked as well.
Was this in Lake Ontario?  Jon
HEY! You big cheater!!  I'm calling the mnr on you cause you violated that poor fishy and then posted him.
You may want to stay silent since you were my main partner in crime during this violation.
Now that's just gross.  You're still a cheater mccheaterson.
That was me landing your fish..  You just snapped a shot of me handing it to you!!
Correction: That fish did not touch my hands :/
I think that's a Belmont Large Regular Cigarette Butt..  Oh you mean the fish.. its just a quillback..
